    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-11-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="446"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Takahira</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-11-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 19, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am informed that Prince Fushimi left Washington yesterday deeply impressed with
                    the manner in which he was welcomed and received by the President and the
                    officials of the United States Government. In expressing my sincere gratitude
                    for the hospitality and courtesy extended to the Prince I beg to assure you, Mr.
                    Secretary, that such a warm reception as was given to our imperial visitor will
                    be always remembered by the whole Japanese nation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">K. Takahira.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
